%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejump%20on%20the%20AI%20train%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20a%20fear-of-missing-out%20rally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20momentum%20and%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20on%20gains%20can%20take%20the%20market%20higher%20over%20the%20short%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said%20in%20a%20weekly%20WisdomTree%20commentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20can%20last%20is%20a%20key%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20long%20can%20such%20optimism%20or%20exuberance%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20bandwagon%26quot%3B%20continue%3F%20If%20we%20argue%20that%20it%20is%20more%20heavily%20driven%20by%20the%20liquidity%20factor%20it%20implies%20that%20such%20FOMO%20behaviour%20can%20morph%20into%20a%20mania%20that%20can%20be%20severely%20out%20of%20synch%20with%20economic%20realities%20akin%20to%20the%20prior%20boom-bust%20cycles%20of%20similar%20high%20technology%20advancement%20narratives%2C%26quot%3B%20OANDA%20analyst%20Kelvin%20Wong%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ERINO%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMove%20over%2C%20bulls%20and%20bears.%20A%20new%20variety%20of%20animal%20spirit%20may%20be%20driving%20the%20market%20now.%20According%20to%20a%20new%20acronym%20coined%20by%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20what%20we%20have%20in%20place%20is%20a%20RINO%20rally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeveloped%20economies%20continue%20to%20surprise%20positively.%20Inflation%20is%20cooling%20down%20and%20a%20soft%20landing%20now%20looks%20like%20a%20plausible%20outcome.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20a%20new%20acronym%20(courtesy%20of%20Goldman)%3A%20the%20%26quot%3BRecession%20In%20Name%20Only%26quot%3B%20(R.I.N.O)%2C%26quot%3B%20analysts%20at%20the%20boutique%20Swiss%20bank%20SYZ%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20much-expected%20US%20recession%20has%20remained%20just%20a%20hypothesis%20and%20not%20a%20reality%2C%20given%20how%20resilient%20the%20economy%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be.%20And%20that's%20a%20cheerful%20enough%20situation%20for%20traders%20to%20pile%20into%20stocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ETINA%20and%20TARA%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20ideas%20that%20have%20had%20some%20influence%20on%20the%20market%20in%202023%20include%20TINA%20(there%20is%20no%20alternative)%20and%20TARA%20(there%20are%20reasonable%20alternatives)%20sentiments%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fwall-street-concedes-there-is-finally-an-alternative-to-stocks-d19aebe6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20argues%20that%20investors%20should%20hold%20on%20to%20stocks%20%E2%80%94%20because%20even%20if%20they%20underwhelm%2C%20there's%20no%20alternative%20asset%20class%20that%20would%20offer%20better%20returns.%20Meanwhile%2C%20TARA%20promotes%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%93%20there%20are%20better%20assets%20to%20invest%20in%20compared%20to%20stocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EYOLO%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20group%20of%20spenders%20are%20keeping%20the%20economy%20afloat%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Feconomy-outlook-yolo-consumers-summer-spending-jobs-report-rate-hikes-2023-7%5C%22%3ESiegel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20high%20interest%20rates%20and%20fears%20of%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20economy%20looks%20like%20it%20is%20progressing%20smoothly%2C%20with%20a%20resilient%20consumer%20impervious%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20higher%20borrowing%20costs.%20It%20is%20the%20'YOLO'%20(you%20only%20live%20once)%20consumer%20out%20traveling%20and%20enjoying%20the%20summer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20a%20separate%20weekly%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wisdomtree.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fus-media-files%2Fdocuments%2Fresource-library%2Fweekly-commentary%2Fsiegel-weekly-commentary.pdf%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2231e03aa363