orking%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20really%20good%20jobs%20out%20there%20except%20for%20the%20unattainable%20or%20the%20menial%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20yeah%2C%20I'm%20very%20grumpy%20lately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-there-was-quiet-quitting-now-its-become-grumpy-staying-2023-6%5C%22%3Egrumpy%20stayers%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3A%20workers%20who%20are%20reluctantly%20staying%20put%20in%20a%20cooling%20labor%20market.%20Grumpy%20stayers%20are%20in%20some%20ways%20the%20next%20iteration%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-great-resignation-trends-economy-outlook-leaving-jobs-davos-2023-1%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rattled%20by%20layoffs%20and%20fewer%20opportunities.%20They%20can't%20skate%20by%20anymore%20or%20be%20as%20vocal%20about%20their%20discontent%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20also%20don't%20want%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalez%20isn't%20alone.%20Some%20of%20these%20workers%20say%20they%20hopped%20into%20%26quot%3Bbetter%26quot%3B%20roles%20that%20didn't%20end%20up%20being%20what%20they'd%20signed%20up%20for.%20Others%20lament%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-shortage-slow-up-great-reshuffle-gen-z-demands-workplace-2021-11%5C%22%3Emissing%20out%20on%20the%20Great%20Reshuffle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20a%20wave%20of%20people%20traded%20up%20jobs%20until%20they%20were%20happy.%20Some%20see%20their%20job%20prospects%20hindered%20by%20unnecessary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ibm-accenture-dell-companies-no-longer-require-college-degrees-2023-3%5C%22%3Edegree%20or%20certification%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20others%20say%20companies%20are%20prioritizing%20perks%20over%20actual%20career%20advancement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%20have%20combined%20to%20create%20a%20situation%20where%20many%20workers%20feel%20stuck.%20The%20Great%20Resignation%20was%20supposed%20to%20help%20them%20gain%20more%20power%2C%20money%2C%20and%20benefits%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-great-resignation-recession-means-workers-powerless-despite-labor-shortage-2022-7%5C%22%3Ethat%20hasn't%20worked%20out%20as%20planned%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%2C%20as%20the%20labor%20market%20cools%2C%20conditions%20are%20ripe%20for%20grumpy%20stayers%20to%20get%20even%20grumpier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20pretty%20much%20stuck%20here%20doing%20this%20work%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20talking%20to%20an%20acquaintance%20of%20mine%20who's%20a%20recruiter%2C%20and%20he's%20telling%20me%20summer%20is%20the%20slow%20time.%20There%20are%20no%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFiltered%20out%20from%20jobs%20that%20might%20make%20them%20happy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGrumpy%20stayers%20come%20in%20many%20forms.%20Some%2C%20like%20Gonzalez%2C%20shuffled%20into%20jobs%20that%20weren't%20as%20good%20a%20fit%20as%20they'd%20hoped.%20Others%2C%20like%20Elizabeth%2C%20a%20barista%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20have%20found%20themselves%20spinning%20in%20the%20same%20role%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20has%20been%20at%20her%20company%20for%2018%20years.%20(Insider%20knows%20her%20last%20name%20and%20employer%20but%20is%20withholding%20them%20for%20privacy%20reasons.)%20She%20said%20she'd%20been%20staying%20at%20her%20role%20out%20of%20inertia.%20She's%20been%20job%20hunting%20for%20a%20year%2C%20even%20for%20just%20a%20second%20part-time%20job%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20find%20anything%20that%20pays%20more%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20what%20I'm%20making%20%E2%80%94%20that%20doesn't%20require%20me%20to%20be%20certified%20or%20have%20a%20degree%20in%20something%20that%20I%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%20she%20found%20herself%20tipping%20over%20the%20grumpy%20edge.%20She%20figured%20she'd%20never%20be%20able%20to%20get%20a%20higher-paying%20position%20without%20spending%20time%20in%20a%20management%20role%2C%20so%20when%20an%20opportunity%20to%20move%20into%20a%20management%20position%20arose%2C%20she%20applied.%20But%20after%20she%20got%20passed%20over%20for%20the%20role%2C%20she%20started%20having%20panic%20attacks%20at%20work%2C%20she%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20at%20one%20point%20she%20almost%20walked%20out%20but%20then%20found%20herself%20sitting%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20crying%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20she's%20on%20leave%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20both%20causing%20and%20exacerbating%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20this%20job%20is%20how%20I%20get%20paid%20leave%20and%20mental-health%20care%20and%20all%20that%20good%20stuff.%20That's%20part%20of%20that%20golden-handcuffs%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20person%20facing%20this%20situation.%20Erica%20Groshen%2C%20a%20senior%20economics%20advisor%20at%20Cornell%20University's%20School%20of%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations%2C%20said%20many%20people%20who%20didn't%20change%20jobs%20have%20%26quot%3Bseen%20a%20lot%20of%20their%20more-mobile%20colleagues%20go%20off%20and%20get%20likely%20to%20be%20higher%20paid%20or%20higher%20benefit%2C%20or%20some%20otherwise%20more%20attractive%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20grumpy%20stayers%20might%20be%20feeling%20left%20behind%2C%20with%20salaries%20lagging%20behind%20those%20of%20their%20peers%20who've%20departed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies'%20actions%20are%20also%20helping%20drive%20the%20trend.%20Groshen%20said%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-jobs-without-degrees-obama-shortage-biden-student-debt-2023-3%5C%22%3Edegree%20or%20credential%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20keeping%20capable%20workers%20from%20getting%20jobs%2C%20even%20at%20a%20time%20when%20firms%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fits-still-a-good-time-to-quit-your-job-layoffs-are-low-2023-7%5C%22%3Estill%20have%20plenty%20of%20job%20openings%20and%20an%20appetite%20to%20hire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENo%20room%20for%20improvement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20theme%20across%20grumpy%20stayers%20is%20that%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20grumpy%2C%20but%20work%20conditions%20make%20them%20that%20way.%20Those%20interviewed%20by%20Insider%20said%20they%20yearned%20for%20advancement%20or%20enrichment%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20a%20way%20to%20convince%20their%20employers%20not%20to%20look%20externally%20for%20new%20hires%20and%20to%20instead%20give%20them%20more%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployer-provided%20training%20is%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20to%20help%20demand%20and%20supply%20match%20up%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Groshen%20said.%20If%20employers%20need%20something%2C%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20can%20take%20their%20staff%20of%20workers%20who%20they%20know%20and%20they%20can%20provide%20them%20with%20the%20skills%20that%20are%20needed%20rather%20than%20laying%20off%20those%20workers%20and%20seeking%20them%20on%20the%20outside%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20worker%20in%20the%20energy%20sector%20in%20Texas%20described%20making%20several%20attempts%20to%20move%20up%20in%20their%20company%20or%20take%20on%20a%20different%20role%20only%20to%20be%20dismissed.%20They%20said%20they%20were%20planning%20to%20stick%20around%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20then%20switch%20careers.%20The%20only%20thing%20keeping%20them%20in%20their%20current%20role%2C%20they%20said%2C%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20mostly%20remote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalez%20is%20facing%20a%20similar%20frustration.%20He'd%20love%20to%20be%20learning%20more%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstanford-university-adding-new-generative-ai-chatgpt-classes-artificial-intelligence-2023-7%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%20and%20new%20technologies%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20has%20found%20himself%20relegated%20to%20helping%20patch%20up%2020-year-old%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrumpiness%20often%20means%20feeling%20undervalued%2C%26quot%3B%20Groshen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20solution%2C%20she%20said%2C%20would%20be%20for%20companies%20to%20engage%20with%20their%20grumpy%20stayers%20and%20lean%20more%20on%20their%20expertise%20to%20solve%20problems.%20%26quot%3BThey%20probably%20know%20a%20lot%20more%20about%20flaws%20and%20how%20to%20prevent%20them%20and%20how%20to%20coordinate%20with%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20operations%20than%20they're%20given%20credit%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Gonzalez%20is%20trying%20to%20work%20through%20his%20frustrations%20in%20a%20healthy%20way.%20He%20said%20he%20quit%20smoking%20%E2%80%94%20his%20old%20method%20of%20dealing%20with%20stress%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%26quot%3Bgot%20a%20little%20rescue%20dog%20to%20at%20least%20give%20me%20some%20comic%20relief%20during%20the%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20have%20the%20dog%20to%20walk%2C%20and%20I%20try%20to%20be%20Zen%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BJust%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20just%20get%20through%20this%20day%2C%20just%20one%20more%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3EAre%20you%20a%20grumpy%20stayer%2C%20or%20fear%20you%20might%20become%20one%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40insider.com%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Ejkaplan%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrumpy-stayers-people-stuck-in-jobs-cant-leave-quiet-quitting-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690108201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b95133245f83001904a9c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrumpy-stayers-people-stuck-in-jobs-cant-leave-quiet-quitting-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20some%20workers%2C%20the%20Great%20Resignation%20didn't%20deliver%20or%20bypassed%20them%20completely.%20Now%20they're%20stuck%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20happy%20about%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrumpy-stayers-people-stuck-in-jobs-cant-leave-quiet-quitting-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Study%20Says%20ChatGPT%20Can%20Match%20The%20Top%201%20%25%20Of%20Creative%20Human%20Thinkers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20new%20research%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2023%2F07%2F230705154051.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUniversity%20of%20Montana%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ChatGPT%2C%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20chatbot%20can%20match%20the%20top%201%20per%20cent%20of%20human%20thinkers%20on%20a%20standard%20test%20of%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20application%2C%20developed%20using%20GPT-4%2C%20excelled%20in%20fluency%20and%20originality%20in%20the%20Torrance%20Tests%20of%20Creative%20Thinking%2C%20a%20widely%20recognised%20tool%20for%20assessing%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20research%2C%20they%20collected%20responses%20from%2024%20University%20of%20Montana%20students.%20The%20scores%20were%20compared%20with%202%2C700%20students%20nationally%20who%20took%20the%20TTCT.%20All%20submissions%20were%20scored%20by%20Scholastic%20Testing%20Service%2C%20which%20didn't%20know%20that%20AI%20was%20involved.%20Then%20the%20scores%20were%20compared%20with%202%2C700%20college%20students%20nationally%20who%20took%20the%20TTCT%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20said%20that%20the%20AI%20responses%20were%20as%20creative%20as%20the%20responses%20from%20the%20most%20creative%20real%20people%20who%20took%20the%20test.%20It%20said%20that%20ChatGPT%20outperformed%20a%20majority%20of%20students%20nationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20ChatGPT%20and%20GPT-4%2C%20we%20showed%20for%20the%20first%20time%20that%20it%20performs%20in%20the%20top%201%25%20for%20originality%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Erik%20Guzik%2C%20an%20assistant%20clinical%20professor%20at%20UM's%20College%20of%20Business%20who%20directed%20the%20study.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20new.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20carefully%20waited%20for%20the%20results%20and%20did%20not%20jump%20to%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20we%20shared%20strong%20evidence%20that%20AI%20seems%20to%20be%20developing%20creative%20ability%20on%20par%20with%20or%20even%20exceeding%20human%20ability%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Guzik%20admitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TTCT%20contains%20different%20assessments%3A%20one%20verbal%20and%20one%20figural.%20Both%20measure%20divergent%20thinking%2C%20or%20the%20thought%20process%20used%20to%20generate%20creative%20ideas%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F07%2F17%2Fstudy-chatgpt-can-match-the-top-1percent-of-creative-human-thinkers.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNBC%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20study%2C%20ChatGPT%20responses%20were%20in%20the%20top%20percentile%20for%20fluency%20and%20originality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20all%20been%20exploring%20with%20ChatGPT%2C%20and%20we%20noticed%20it%20had%20been%20doing%20some%20interesting%20things%20that%20we%20didn't%20expect%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Guzik%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20responses%20were%20novel%20and%20surprising.%20That's%20when%20we%20decided%20to%20put%20it%20to%20the%20test%20to%20see%20how%20creative%20it%20really%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690108020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fb8ea8jsg_chatgpt_625x300_26_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstudy-says-chatgpt-can-match-the-top-1-of-creative-human-thinkers-4233948%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20study%2C%20ChatGPT%20responses%20were%20in%20the%20top%20percentile%20for%20fluency%20and%20original%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstudy-says-chatgpt-can-match-the-top-1-of-creative-human-thinkers-4233948%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstudy-says-chatgpt-can-match-the-top-1-of-creative-human-thinkers-4233948%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstudy-says-chatgpt-can-match-the-top-1-of-creative-human-thinkers-4233948%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kishan%20A%20Prey%20Of%20%5C%22T20%20Or%20White-ball%20Effect%5C%22%3F%20India%20Legend%20Gives%20This%20Logic%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Test%20series%20against%20West%20Indies%20has%20seen%20the%20Indian%20team%20management%20give%20chances%20to%20new%20faces.%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Yashasvi%20Jaiswal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F112646-yashasvi-jaiswal-playerprofile%5C%22%3EYashasvi%20Jaiswal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Mukesh%20Kumar%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F108561-mukesh-kumar-playerprofile%5C%22%3EMukesh%20Kumar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ishan%20Kishan%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F107047-ishan-kishan-playerpr