on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20(UoK)%2C%20the%20Valley%E2%80%99s%20premier%20higher-educational%20institution%2C%20has%20dropped%20three%20poems%20by%20Kashmiri-American%20poet%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%20along%20with%20author%20and%20journalist%20Basharat%20Peer%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20from%20the%20curriculum%20of%20a%20post-graduate%20programme%20in%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShahid%E2%80%99s%20famous%20poems%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Postcard%20from%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98In%20Arabic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Last%20Saffron%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Peer%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENight%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20taught%20in%20the%20third%20semester%20of%20the%20Masters%20of%20Arts%20(English)%20course%20at%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20works%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20part%20of%20the%20curriculum%20from%20this%20year%20onwards%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20source%20at%20the%20university%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20decision%20was%20conveyed%20%E2%80%9Corally%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Crelevant%20authorities%20after%20consultations%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Vice-Chancellor%E2%80%99s%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20university%20has%20also%20removed%20the%20syllabus%20of%20the%20two-year%20masters%20programme%20from%20its%20website.%20Sources%20said%20that%20the%20syllabus%20will%20become%20accessible%20%E2%80%9Conce%20it%20has%20been%20updated.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20deletions%2C%20Professor%20Nilofer%20Khan%2C%20UoK%20Vice-Chancellor%2C%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20meeting%E2%80%9D%20and%20promised%20to%20get%20back.%20She%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20phone%20calls%20made%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20decision%20to%20discontinue%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20two%20poems%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20see%20Kashmir%20from%20New%20Delhi%20at%20Midnight%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Call%20me%20Ishmael%20Tonight%2C%E2%80%99%20was%20taken%20by%20the%20Cluster%20University%20Srinagar%20(CUS)%2C%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98I%20see%20Kashmir%20from%20New%20Delhi%20at%20Midnight%E2%80%99%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20iconic%20explorations%20of%20the%20struggles%20faced%20by%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20since%20armed%20insurgency%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20early%20nineties.%20The%20poem%20touches%20on%20issues%20of%20torture%2C%20%E2%80%98bullet-torn%E2%80%99%20bodies%20and%20%E2%80%98curfewed%20nights%E2%80%99%20that%20were%20a%20recurrent%20theme%20of%20life%20in%20Kashmir%20during%20the%20heydays%20of%20insurgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Call%20me%20Ishmael%20Tonight%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20poignant%20ghazal%20with%20allegedly%20blasphemous%20references%20in%20which%20Shahid%20tries%20to%20locate%20himself%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20religion%20and%20the%20conflict%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20ghazal%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20destruction%20of%20some%20Hindu%20temples%20in%20the%20Valley%20when%20the%20conflict%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20poems%20were%20taught%20in%20the%20third%20semester%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Integrated%20Masters%20in%20English%E2%80%99%20programme%20at%20the%20CUS.%20Among%20other%20poets%20whose%20works%20are%20taught%20in%20the%20programme%20are%20the%20influential%20Urdu%20poet%2C%20Faiz%20Ahmad%20Faiz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20syllabus%20for%20the%20five-year%20programme%20has%20not%20been%20updated%20yet%20and%20it%20is%20still%20accessible%20on%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20official%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20official%20explanation%20for%20the%20deletions%20and%20no%20order%20was%20passed%20in%20either%20of%20the%20instances.%20Professor%20Qayyum%20Hussain%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnVice-Chancellor%20of%20CUS%2C%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20his%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20academic%20at%20the%20UOK%20said%20that%20Shahid%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20secular%20poet%20whose%20heart%20was%20full%20of%20pain%20and%20anguish%20for%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%E2%80%9D%20of%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CAlthough%20his%20work%20touches%20on%20the%20themes%20of%20Kashmir%20conflict%2C%20the%20three%20poems%20(taught%20at%20UOK)%20have%20absolutely%20no%20political%20connotations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmaulana-azad-jammu-kashmir-ncert-dropped%5C%22%3ERevised%20NCERT%20Textbook%20Drops%20Statement%20That%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Accession%20Was%20Based%20on%20Promise%20of%20Autonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgha%20Shahid%20Ali%3A%20%E2%80%98A%20voice%20like%20no%20other%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20widely%20read%20Kashmiri%20writers%20in%20English%2C%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%202001%20poetry%20collection%2C%20%3Cem%3ERooms%20are%20Never%20Finished%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0was%20the%20finalist%20for%20the%20National%20Book%20Award%2C%20the%20prestigious%20US%20literary%20prize%20whose%20winners%20include%20the%201949%20Nobel%20laureate%20William%20Faulkner%20and%20Pulitzer%20awardees%20Philip%20Roth%20and%20John%20Updike%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20United%20States%20where%20he%20died%20of%20brain%20cancer%20in%202001%20aged%2052%2C%20Shahid%20was%20an%20alumnus%20of%20the%20UoK%20who%20had%20fulfilling%20teaching%20stints%20at%20the%20Delhi%20University%2C%20Princeton%20University%20and%20Hamilton%20College%20among%20other%20reputed%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EAmerican%20Alphabets%3A%2025%20Contemporary%20Poets%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20major%20anthology%20of%20American%20poetry%2C%20describes%20Shahid%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cextraordinary%20poets%20born%20since%20World%20War%20II.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20voice%20was%20like%20none%20I%20had%20ever%20heard%20before%2C%20at%20once%20lyrical%20and%20fiercely%20disciplined%2C%20engaged%20and%20yet%20deeply%20inward%E2%80%A6the%20formalisation%20of%20the%20ghazal%20may%20well%20prove%20to%20be%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20scholarly%20contribution%20to%20the%20canon%20of%20English%20poetry%2C%E2%80%9D%20author%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Ghat%20of%20The%20Only%20World%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essay%2C%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20tribute%20to%20his%20Kashmiri%20friend%2C%20which%20was%20published%20after%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20School%20Education%E2%80%99s%20Class%2011%20curriculum%20which%20is%20taught%20at%20more%20than%2027%2C000%20schools%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20tragedy%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20UOK%20official%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20fearing%20reprisal%20from%20the%20authorities%2C%20%E2%80%9CStudents%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20read%20about%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%20but%20doing%20so%20in%20Kashmir%20is%20unacceptable%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBasharat%20Peer%3A%20%E2%80%98Brutally%20honest%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeer%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20deeply%20personal%20and%20groundbreaking%20memoir%20of%20growing%20up%20in%20violence-ravaged%20Kashmir%2C%20received%20critical%20acclaim%20for%20drawing%20an%20unforgettable%20image%20of%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20Himalayan%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthor%20Khushwant%20Singh%20had%20called%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENight%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20%E2%80%9Cbrutally%20honest%20and%20deeply%20hurtful%E2%80%9D%20account%20while%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20said%20it%20brings%20the%20%E2%80%9CKashmir%20conflict%20out%20of%20the%20realm%20of%20political%20rhetoric%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20and%20into%20the%20lives%20of%20Kashmiris.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20memoir%20took%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20English%20writing%20scene%20by%20a%20storm%20when%20it%20debuted%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELondon-based%20Kashmiri%20writer%20and%20acclaimed%20novelist%20Mirza%20Waheed%20said%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20drop%20the%20two%20authors%20%E2%80%9Creinforces%E2%80%9D%20the%20idea%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20being%20run%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20anti-intellectual%20and%20anti-thought%E2%80%9D%20administration.%20%E2%80%9CI%20suppose%20these%20days%20it%20must%20look%20good%20on%20a%20university%20administrators%E2%80%99s%20CV%20to%20say%20they%20removed%20a%20beautiful%20poet%20from%20their%20campus.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20is%20the%20Chancellor%20and%20de-facto%20head%20of%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20terrible%20and%20sinister%20decision%2C%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20push%20to%20create%20%E2%80%98Naya%20(new)%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%20which%20means%20erasure%20of%20history%20%E2%80%93%20that%20we%20forget%20our%20history%2C%20our%20political%20and%20cultural%20heritage%2C%20our%20poets.%20It%20is%20a%20war%20on%20memory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Waheed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWaheed%2C%20author%20of%20the%20novel%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Collaborator%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20universities%20are%20a%20%E2%80%9Cplace%20of%20knowledge%2C%20thinking%20and%20critical%20engagement%20with%20literature%E2%80%9D%20which%20helps%20students%20in%20%E2%80%9Clocating%20themselves%20in%20the%20broader%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShahid%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20has%20been%20read%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20across%20the%20world%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20it%20will%20be%20read%20even%20more.%20Basharat%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20books%20of%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%C2%A0You%20can%E2%80%99t%20erase%20Shahid%20from%20memory.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%3Cem%3E%20Curfewed%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%20disappear%2C%E2%80%9D%20Waheed%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690103524000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23143508%2FUntitled-design-6-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkashmir-university-agha-shahid-ali-basharat-peer-dropped%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20University%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20Valley%E2%80%99s%20premier%20higher-educational%20institution%2C%20has%20dropped%20three%20poems%20by%20Ali%20along%20and%20journalist%20Basharat%20Peer%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20from%20its%20English%20MA%20curriculum.%20The%20Cluster%20University%20Srinagar%20has%20left%20out%20two%20poems%20by%20Ali.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkashmir-university-agha-shahid-ali-basharat-peer-dropped%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20rights%20do%20holidaymakers%20have%20as%20Rhodes%20wildfires%20force%20thousands%20to%20flee%20hotels%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690103100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F768x432%2Fskynews-rhodes-greece-wildfires_6227614.jpg%3F20230723105933%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frhodes-wildfires-what-rights-do-holidaymakers-have-as-thousands-forced-to-flee-hotels-12925912%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Raging%20wildfires%20on%20the%20Greek%20island%20of%20Rhodes%20have%20sparked%20the%20evacuation%20of%20around%202%2C000%20tourists%20from%20its%20resorts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frhodes-wildfires-what-rights-do-holidaymakers-have-as-thousands-forced-to-flee-hotels-12925912%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Frhodes-wildfires-what-rights-do-holidaymakers-have-as-thousands-forced-to-flee-hotels-12925912%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Frhodes-wildfires-what-rights-do-holidaymakers-have-as-thousands-forced-to-flee-hotels-12925912%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bail%20Can't%20Be%20Refused%20As%20Indirect%20Punishment%3A%20Delhi%20Court%20In%20Bribery%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Delhi%20court%20has%20said%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20as%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20an%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%20while%20releasing%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpecial%20Judge%20Sunena%20Sharma%20granted%20bail%20to%20Rishi%20Raj%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20criminal%20jurisprudence%20that%20an%20accused%20is%20presumed%20to%20be%20innocent%20until%20proven%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20criminal%20jurisprudence%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20presumed%20to%20be%20innocent%20until%20proven%20guilty.%20Even%20assuming%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20prima%20facie%20guilty%20of%20an%20offence%2C%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20in%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20the%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20in%20the%20order%20passed%20on%20July%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20accused%20was%20in%20judicial%20custody%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%20and%20the%20audio%20and%20video%20recordings%20of%20the%20alleged%20transaction%20were%20already%20in%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20accused%20was%20a%20public%20servant%20and%20had%20no%20previous%20involvement%20in%20any%20such%20matter%2C%20though%20he%20was%20under%20suspension%20on%20account%20of%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20the%20apprehension%20of%20the%20CBI%20that%20the%20accused%20may%20flee%20from%20justice%20or%20influence%20the%20witnesses%20is%20without%20any%20basis.%20Moreover%2C%20if%20the%20accused%20is%20found%20misusing%20bail%20by%20indulging%20in%20any%20such%20acts%2C%20the%20CBI%20may%20approach%20this%20court%20for%20cancellation%20of%20bail%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20granted%20the%20relief%20to%20the%20accused%20on%20a%20bail%20bond%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20with%20two%20sureties%20of%20a%20like%20amount%20and%20directed%20that%20the%20accused%20will%20not%20leave%20the%20country%20without%20the%20court's%20permission%20nor%20will%20he%20contact%20or%20influence%20the%20witnesses%20in%20any%20manner%20and%20will%20cooperate%20in%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20registered%20by%20the%20CBI%20on%20June%2012%20under%20sections%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20complaint%20from%20one%20Manoj%20Kumar%20Sheora%2C%20manager%20at%20the%20Gupta%20Multi-Speciality%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complainant%20had%20alleged%20that%20Raj%2C%20who%20was%20working%20as%20an%20enforcement%20officer%20in%20the%20Employees'%20Provident%20Fund%20Organisation%20(EPFO)%2C%20visited%20the%20hospital%20on%20April%2026%20and%20asked%20for%20documents%20related%20to%20records%20regarding%20the%20provident%20fund%20of%20the%20hospitals'%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2027%2C%20the%20complainant%20visited%20the%20EPFO%20office%20and%20produced%20the%20relevant%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20accused%20told%20the%20complainant%20about%20irregularities%20in%20the%20records%20and%20that%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%201.5%20crore%20would%20be%20imposed%20on%20account%20of%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20proposed%20to%20settle%20the%20matter%20without%20any%20penalty%20on%20the%20payment%20of%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20amount%20as%20bribe%2C%20which%20he%20reduced%20to%20Rs%2012%20lakh%20on%20the%20request%20of%20the%20complainant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complainant%20subsequently%20filed%20the%20complaint.%20A%20trap%20was%20laid%20and%20the%20accused%20was%20arrested%20while%20taking%20the%20bribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20sought%20bail%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20accused%20had%20the%20responsibility%20to%20look%20after%20his%20aged%20parents%20and%20wife%2C%20who%20is%20seven%20months%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20also%20claimed%20that%20no%20fruitful%20purpose%20would%20be%20served%20by%20further%20keeping%20him%20in%20custody%20as%20the%20investigation%20was%20almost%20complete%20and%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20join%20the%20probe%20as%20and%20when%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690102980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fcourt-generic_625x300_1527245477936.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Delhi%20court%20has%20said%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20as%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20an%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%20while%20releasing%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%