2Fstrong%3E%20Condemning%20the%20%E2%80%9Cescalating%20attacks%E2%80%9D%20on%20minorities%20in%20India%2C%20US%20Congresswoman%20Rashida%20Tlaib%C2%A0said%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Cproud%E2%80%9D%20to%20have%20boycotted%20the%20address%20of%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20the%20joint%20sitting%20of%20US%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20Congressional%20briefing%20organised%20by%2018%20civil%20society%20groups%20on%20July%2019%2C%20Congresswoman%20Rashida%20Tlaib%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20proud%20to%20have%20stood%20with%20my%20colleagues%20in%20boycotting%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20speech%20%5Bduring%20his%20US%20visit%5D.%20This%20House%20should%20never%20be%20used%20as%20a%20platform%20to%20spread%20bigotry%20and%20hate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F06%2F22%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fmodi-speech-biden-boycott.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%20half%20a%20dozen%20Democrats%20had%20boycotted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20speech%20by%20Modi%20last%20month%2C%20over%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20human%20rights%20record%20when%20it%20came%20to%20minorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20witnessed%20severe%20escalating%20attacks%20on%20religious%20minorities%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%A6%20And%20yet%20we%20know%20our%20own%20US%20State%20Department%20has%20yet%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%20under%20US%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20as%20per%20a%20press%20release%20on%20the%20briefing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bi-partisan%20US%20state-department%20funded%20US%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20(USCIRF)%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fuscirf-country-of-particular-concern-fourth-time%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecommended%20for%20four%20consecutive%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20India%20should%20be%20designated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20State%20department.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20now%2C%20the%20US%20state%20department%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20any%20such%20action.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20accused%20USCIRF%20of%20reiterating%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-lashes-out-uscirf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebiased%20and%20motivated%20comments%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20country%20in%20its%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20briefing%2C%20USCIRF%20Commissioner%20David%20Curry%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Commission%20had%20urged%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20raise%20religious%20freedom%20concerns%20during%20the%20Indian%20PM%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CReligious%20freedom%20was%20mentioned%20briefly%20during%20the%20visit%20but%20was%20certainly%20not%20a%20focal%20point%E2%80%A6%20Modi%20denied%20that%20discrimination%20of%20religious%20minorities%20existed%20in%20India.%20We%20strongly%20disagree%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconta.cc%2F3PYKTHO%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epress%20communique%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20organisers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20PM%20had%20been%20asked%20a%20question%20about%20the%20state%20of%20minorities%20at%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbiden-by-his-side-modi-cites-constitution-to-parry-question-on-minority-rights-suppression-of-dissent%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erare%20press%20interaction%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20White%