ates%20that%20wages%20and%20earnings%20have%20stagnated%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years%20(Figure%201).%20This%20finding%20needs%20to%20be%20read%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20NSO%E2%80%99s%20Employment-Unemployment%20Round%20between%202004-5%20and%202011-12%20had%20shown%20a%20sustained%20rise%20in%20real%20wages.%20However%2C%20they%20stagnated%20in%202013-2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20fairly%20easy%20to%20understand%20why%20real%20wages%20have%20either%20stagnated%20or%20fallen%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20The%20period%202017-18%20was%20the%20year%20following%20demonetisation%20in%20late%202016%2C%20which%20had%20caused%20widespread%20damage%20to%20large%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20especially%20agricultural%20incomes%20as%20well%20as%20the%20entire%20unorganised%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20the%20economy%20emerged%20from%20demonetisation%2C%20a%20poorly%20designed%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20was%20introduced%20in%20July%202017%2C%20which%20subsumed%2017%20other%20central%20and%20state%20taxes.%20It%20caused%20widespread%20disruption%2C%20again%20to%20the%20unorganised%20sector%2C%20and%20especially%20to%20MSMEs%2C%20which%20were%20even%20less%20prepared%20to%20make%20the%20transition.%20The%20economy%20went%20into%20a%20gradual%20slowdown%2C%20with%20GDP%20falling%20in%20every%20quarter%20continuously%20till%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoblessness%20had%20reached%20a%2045-year%20high%20in%202017-18%20and%20with%20the%20continuous%20slowdown%2C%20joblessness%20continued%20to%20increase.%20Ten%20million%20were%20unemployed%20in%202011-12%3B%20it%20rose%20to%2030%20million%20by%202018-19%2C%20before%20COVID-19%20broke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20began%20with%20a%20lockdown%20announced%20at%20four%20hours%E2%80%99%20notice%20for%20nearly%201.4%20billion%20people%2C%20and%20brought%20the%20entire%20economy%20and%20transportation%20to%20a%20standstill.%20This%20pushed%20unemployment%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20third%20claim%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20senior-most%20government%20economic%20adviser%20has%20claimed%20that%20because%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20growth%20rate%20has%20fallen%20to%200.8%25%20pa%20and%20the%20total%20fertility%20rate%20fell%20to%202%20(below%20the%20replacement%20rate%20of%202.1)%20in%202021%2C%20India%20does%20not%20need%20to%20create%2010%20mn%20jobs%20a%20year.%20This%20claim%20assumes%20that%20those%20born%20today%20will%20start%20to%20work%20very%20shortly%2C%20which%20is%20obviously%20wrong.%20It%20takes%20them%2015%20years%20from%20birth%20to%20even%20complete%20eight%20years%20of%20education%2C%20and%20legally%20enter%20the%20labour%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20also%20ignores%20three%20facts%20of%20critical%20significance%20to%20job%20creation.%20First%2C%20India%20needed%20to%20pull%20millions%20out%20of%20agriculture%20even%20before%20the%20catastrophic%20reverse%20migrations%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20who%20were%20underemployed%20(%3E42%25%20of%20workforce%20generating%2015%25%20of%20GDP).%20Because%20non-farm%20jobs%20were%20not%20growing%20fast%20enough%20to%20absorb%20the%20numbers%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20in%20agriculture%20rose%20even%20in%202022%20(PLFS)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20a%20government%20economist%20calls%20%E2%80%98jobful%E2%80%99%20growth.%20The%20share%20of%20workers%20in%20agriculture%20fell%20from%2060%25%20in%202000%20to%2042%25%20in%202019%2C%20and%20shot%20up%20to%2045.6%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20group%20that%20need%20non-farm%20jobs%20are%20youth%2C%20who%20are%20getting%20better%20education%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20century%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20work%20in%20agriculture%2C%20given%20continuing%20rural%20distress.%20Girls%20had%20achieved%20a%20gross%20enrolment%20rate%20of%2080%25%20in%20secondary%20education%20by%202015.%20They%20aspire%20to%20marry%20later%20than%20age%2018%2C%20as%20a%20Nandi%20Foundation%20survey%20of%20teenagers%20had%20found%20(75%25%20want%20to%20marry%20at%2018-25%20years).%20Yet%2C%20India%20has%20the%20lowest%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20in%20the%20world%2C%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20third%20group%20needing%20non-farm%20jobs%20are%20the%20openly%20unemployed.%20The%20current%20government%20inherited%20about%2010%20mn%20unemployed%3B%20that%20number%20grew%20to%2030%20mn%2C%20we%20estimate%2C%20by%202019.%20Thanks%20to%20poor%20economic%20management%20during%20COVID-19%2C%20and%20a%20K-shaped%20recovery%2C%20open%20unemployment%20grew%20to%2038%20million%20by%202022%20(PLFS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sum%2C%20India%20needs%20at%20least%2010-12%20mn%20new%20jobs%20each%20year%20at%20least%20until%202030%2C%20after%20which%20the%20number%20of%20new%20entrants%20to%20the%20labour%20force%20could%20decline%20due%20to%20the%20slowing%20of%20population%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EProfessor%20%3Cspan%3ESantosh%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EMehrotra%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20editor%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fab924bf2-3b47-4f45-8dfd-838535368c9d%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fab924bf2-3b47-4f45-8dfd-838535368c9d%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1690173811212000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2jUbDyFt1P_NSa9LNBdioY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReviving%20Jobs%3A%20An%20Agenda%20for%20Growth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Penguin%2C%202020%2C%20soon%20to%20be%20out%20also%20in%20Hindi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20pre