5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20focuses%20on%20Robbie%E2%80%99s%20Barbie%20%E2%80%93%20who%20starts%20%E2%80%98malfunctioning%E2%80%99%2C%20after%20she%20wakes%20up%20with%20bad%20breath%2C%20and%20begins%20to%20have%20thoughts%20of%20death.%20We%E2%80%99re%20also%20introduced%20to%20Ken%20(Ryan%20Gosling)%2C%20who%20lives%20only%20to%20get%20Barbie%E2%80%99s%20attention.%20When%20Barbie%20realises%20the%20only%20way%20to%20rectify%20the%20cellulite%20on%20her%20skin%20(and%20the%20%E2%80%98weird%E2%80%99%20thoughts%20she%E2%80%99s%20having)%2C%20is%20to%20go%20to%20the%20real%20world%20and%20meet%20the%20person%20playing%20with%20her%2C%20to%20fix%20the%20%E2%80%98space-time%E2%80%99%20continuum%20between%20Barbie%20Land%20and%20the%20real%20world%2C%20Ken%20accompanies%20her%20%E2%80%93%20an%20act%20of%20reckless%2C%20selfless%20kindness.%20Gosling%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century%20in%20the%20film%20business%20hearing%20about%20his%20%E2%80%98Ken%20doll%E2%80%99%20looks%2C%20is%20disarmingly%20sincere%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20reach%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California%2C%20which%20is%20also%20which%20is%20the%20headquarters%20of%20Mattel%2C%20the%20company%20manufacturing%20Barbie%20and%20Ken.%20It%E2%80%99s%20in%20this%20section%20of%20the%20film%20when%20it%20scores%20its%20highest.%20Both%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20are%20coming%20to%20realise%20that%20the%20real%20world%20might%20be%20just%20a%20%3Cem%3Elittle%3C%2Fem%3E%20different%20from%20what%20they%E2%80%99d%20imagined.%20Gerwig%20keeps%20the%20tone%20light%20even%20as%20both%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20try%20to%20navigate%20the%20absolute%20opposite%20notions%20of%20the%20genders%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20Over%20here%2C%20men%20run%20things.%20Teenage%20girls%20hate%20dolls%20for%20setting%20unachievable%20standards%20for%20appearances.%20Barbie%20breaks%20down%20on%20learning%20that%20the%20world%20treats%20her%20with%20disrespect%20because%20of%20her%20gender%2C%20while%20Ken%20seems%20to%20be%20enjoying%20all%20the%20new-found%20attention%20he%20gets%20for%20the%20way%20he%20looks%20(and%20also%20his%20gender).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGosling%20is%20a%20hoot%20as%20someone%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20control%20his%20joy%20after%20%E2%80%98discovering%E2%80%99%20patriarchy%2C%20realising%20the%20real%20world%20values%20him.%20Gosling%20is%20completely%20believable%20as%20he%20sells%20his%20big%2C%20doofus%20smile%20reaching%20the%20conclusion%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20he%20who%20deserves%20to%20be%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Barbieland%2C%20soon%20to%20be%20renamed%20%E2%80%98Kendom%E2%80%99.%20Robbie%20is%20earnest%20as%20the%20most%20perfect-looking%20person%20to%20have%20ever%20existed%2C%20striving%20to%20be%20more%20than%20her%20looks.%20If%20both%20%3Cem%3EBabylon%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20and%20this%20are%20anything%20to%20go%20by%2C%20nobody%20can%20cry%20better%20than%20her.%20Ironically%2C%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20isn%E2%80%99t%20able%20to%20give%20Robbie%20her%20own%20distinct%20flavour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20conceit%20of%20%3Cem%3EBarbie%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20viewing%20the%20age-old%20battle%20of%20sexes%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20the%20equal%20rights%20movement%2C%20is%20an%20interesting%20one.%20It%20succeeds%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20taking%20two%20central%20figures%20who%20defined%20%E2%80%98masculinity%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98femininity%E2%80%99%20for%20an%20entire%20generation%20and%20investigating%20their%20gender%20roles%20in%20a%20Utopian%20setting.%20It%20never%20muddies%20itself%20with%20in-between%20nuances.%20It%E2%80%99s%20either%20war%20between%20Barbies%20and%20Kens%20or%20one%20set%20dominating%20the%20other.%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20addresses%20co-existence%2C%20as%20Barbies%20and%20Kens%20discover%20lives%20beyond%20their%20primary%20%E2%80%98functions%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20they%20mostly%20feel%20like%20feeble%20nudges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20disingenuous%20things%20about%20the%20film%20is%20the%20involvement%20of%20Mattel%20%E2%80%93%20which%2C%20while%20at%20one%20level%20can%20be%20perceived%20as%20a%20company%20introspecting%20about%20its%20capitalist%20history%20%E2%80%93%20could%20also%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20company%20trying%20to%20leverage%20its%20%E2%80%9Cself-awareness%E2%80%9D%20for%20image%20purposes.%20Will%20Ferrell%20%E2%80%93%20in%20a%20sensational%20cameo%20%E2%80%93%20plays%20the%20whimsical%2C%20greedy%20CEO%2C%20who%20chases%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Barbieland.%20The%20pitch%20of%20%3Cem%3EBarble%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20cartoonishly%20high%2C%20which%20Ferrell%20effortlessly%20matches.%20However%2C%20if%20Greta%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20an%20indictment%20of%20set%20gender%20roles%20and%20men%E2%80%99s%20greed%20fuelling%20those%20notions%2C%20the%20final%20film%20ends%20up%20feeling%20more%20like%20a%20gentle%20reprimand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%2C%20%3Cem%3EBarbie%3C%2Fem%3E%20commits%20the%20cardinal%20sin%3A%20it%20talks%20down%20to%20its%20audience.%20America%20Ferrera%20goes%20on%20a%20feminist%20monologue%20bender%20%E2%80%98turning%E2%80%99%20brainwashed%20and%20servile%20Barbies%20into%20their%20original%20selves.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20speech%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20written%20by%20someone%20who%20saw%20screenshots%20of%20the%20Laura%20Dern%20monologue%20from%20%3Cem%3EMarriage%20Story%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2019)%20on%20Twitter.%20No%20surprise%20then%20that%20the%20director%20of%20%3Cem%3EMarriage%20Story%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20Noah%20Baumbach%20(also%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20long-time%20partner)%20is%20credited%20as%20co-writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreta%20Gerwig%20is%20a%20talented%2C%20fun%20filmmaker%20%E2%80%93%20who%20knows%20a%20thing%20or%20three%20about%20a%20good%20adaptation.%20Her%20last%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3ELittle%20Women%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2019)%20is%20proof.%20It%E2%80%99s%20unfortunate%20that%20in%20a%20film%20where%20she%20goads%20her%20characters%20to%20find%20themselves%2C%20her%20creative%20voice%20is%20flattened%20out%20by%20a%20corporation%E2%80%99s.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690046454000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F22223249%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-22T223230.691.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fits-a-barbie-world-but-only-as-a-fantasy-in-real-life-patriarchy-rules%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Director%20Greta%20Gerwig%20commits%20the%20cardinal%20sin%20by%20talking%20down%20to%20its%20audience.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fits-a-barbie-world-but-only-as-a-fantasy-in-real-life-patriarchy-rules%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20%E2%80%98Oppenheimer%E2%80%99%20Pulled%20Off%20an%20Atomic%20Bomb%20Explosion%20Without%20CGI%3A%20A%20Giant%20Aquarium%2C%20Balloons%20and%20More%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690044900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FGF-11507_MSG-e1689977930404.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D562%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235676487%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202020%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CTenet%2C%E2%80%9D%20Christopher%20Nolan%20blew%20up%20a%20747%2C%20and%20for%20his%20latest%20feature%2C%20%E2%80%9COppenheimer%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recreated%20the%20Trinity%20Test%20without%20using%20visual%20effects%2C%20opting%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20do%20it%20in-camera%20instead.%20%E2%80%9CObviously%2C%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20make%20an%20explosion%20the%20size%20of%20the%20actual%20explosion%20so%20we%20used%20trickery%2C%E2%80%9D%20cinematographer%20Hoyte%20van%20Hoytema%20explains%2C%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Jazztangcay%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalU