ds%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-1689666293-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-1689666293-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-1689666293-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-1689666293-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324146%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EShashank%20says%20it%20costs%20Rs%20800%20per%20sq%20ft%20to%20establish%20an%20aquaponics%20terrace%20farm%20in%20a%20vertical%20setup.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20this%2C%20he%20suggests%20farmers%20introduce%20fish%20like%20gold%20and%20koi%20fish.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20produce%20more%20excreta%20and%20also%20survive%20in%20harsh%20temperature%20conditions.%20Just%20ensure%20to%20filter%20the%20water%20before%20adding%20the%20fish%20to%20the%20tank%3B%20water%20should%20not%20be%20hard.%20You%20can%20add%20150%20fish%20in%20a%201%2C000-litre%20tank.%20For%20edible%20fish%2C%20you%20would%20require%20a%20tank%20of%203%2C000%20litres%20as%20their%20size%20grows%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShashank%20says%20it%20costs%20Rs%20800%20per%20sq%20ft%20to%20establish%20an%20aquaponics%20terrace%20farm%20in%20a%20vertical%20setup.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20cost%20can%20be%20reduced%20to%20Rs%20400%20if%20farmers%20wish%20to%20avoid%20vertical%20farming.%20It%20is%20a%20one-time%20investment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFood%20production%20is%20basic%20yet%20urban%20residents%20avert%20from%20the%20idea.%20Instead%20of%20earning%20a%20good%20income%20for%20myself%2C%20my%20focus%20is%20on%20enabling%20urban%20Indians%20to%20grow%20their%20own%20vegetables%20even%20if%20they%20have%20a%20small%20space%20%E2%80%94%20as%20small%20as%20one%20square%20foot%2C%20The%20aquaponics%20farming%20will%20enable%20people%20to%20decentralise%20food%20production%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shashank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20wish%20to%20learn%20aquaponics%20farming%2C%20you%20can%20contact%20Shashank%20at%20%2B91%2099742%2004501.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689687228000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-2-1689666156.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D324007%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vadodara-resident%20Shashank%20Chaubey%20quit%20his%20comfortable%20job%20to%20grow%20vegetables%20using%20aquaponics%20farming.%20Having%20started%20with%20zero%20farming%20experience%2C%20today%20he%20grows%202%2C500%20varieties%20of%20plants%20on%20a%202%2C000%20sq%20ft%20commercial%20terrace%20farm%20and%20helps%20other%20people%20do%20the%20same.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F324007%2Fvadodara-engineer-quit-job-to-grow-vegetables-at-home-terrace-aquaponics-farming%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Forgotten%20Indian%20Who%20Made%20Nobel%20Laureate%20Ronald%20Ross%E2%80%99%20Malaria%20Breakthrough%20Possible%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20speak%20of%20the%20role%20of%20Indian%20men%20and%20women%20in%20shaping%20the%20medical%20world%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323582%2Fmanzilat-descendant-of-wajid-ali-shah-keeps-family-history-of-kolkata-biryani-alive%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompelling%20stories%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20come%20to%20light%20is%20arguably%20that%20of%20Kishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%20and%20his%20role%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20malaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20science%20graduate%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20tackling