w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDaera-X-Cancelled-Plans-1689080816-500x889.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDaera-X-Cancelled-Plans-1689080816-768x1365.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDaera-X-Cancelled-Plans-1689080816-864x1536.jpg%20864w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDaera-X-Cancelled-Plans-1689080816-150x267.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-323405%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EL%20to%20R%3A%20Sharon%2C%20Mallika%20and%20Jannat%2C%20the%20trio%20behind%20the%20collaborative%20collection%20Daera%20X%20Cancelled%20Plans%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Sharon%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20waste%20is%20sourced%20from%20industrial%20areas%20in%20and%20around%20Delhi%20and%20Hyderabad.%20%E2%80%9CHaving%20lived%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20I%20am%20familiar%20with%20the%20manufacturing%20industries%20here.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20started%20sourcing%20waste%20from%20the%20same%20pharmaceutical%20company%20where%20I%20worked.%20We%20collect%20the%20non-hazardous%20waste%20from%20these%20companies.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20the%20packaging%20of%20tablets%2C%20plastic%20wraps%2C%20the%20shredded%20bits%20that%20come%20out%20as%20the%20machines%20are%20cutting%20off%20tablets%2C%20empty%20containers%2C%20etc.%20Waste%20from%20the%20other%20factories%20includes%20textile%20waste%2C%20extra%20material%20obtained%20from%20billboard%20printing%20companies%2C%20and%20many%20other%20such%20kinds%20of%20waste.%C2%A0Mallika%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20prevented%20500%20kg%20of%20waste%20from%20entering%20into%20landfills%20by%20repurposing%20it%20for%20our%20products.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20waste%20material%20is%20ready%2C%20the%20next%20part%20of%20the